# Project: Regency at Summerlin Real Estate Website
# Owner: Dr. Jan Duffy, Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Nevada Properties

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 15 (App Router)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS 4.0
- Deployment: Vercel
- CMS: Headless (or static)
- IDX Integration: RealScout Office Listings Widget
- Analytics: Google Analytics 4, Google Search Console
- Forms: React Hook Form with Zod validation

## RealScout IDX Widget Integration (CRITICAL)
Agent Encoded ID: QWdlbnQtMjI1MDUw

### Head Script (add to layout.tsx or _document.tsx):
<script src="https://em.realscout.com/widgets/realscout-web-components.umd.js" type="module"></script>

### Widget Styling (add to globals.css):
realscout-office-listings {
  --rs-listing-divider-color: #1a365d;  /* Match our navy primary */
  width: 100%;
}

### Default Widget Configuration:
<realscout-office-listings 
  agent-encoded-id="QWdlbnQtMjI1MDUw" 
  sort-order="NEWEST" 
  listing-status="For Sale" 
  property-types=",SFR" 
  price-min="400000" 
  price-max="1100000">
</realscout-office-listings>

### Widget Variants by Page:
- Homepage: price-min="700000" price-max="1100000" (Regency range)
- General listings: price-min="400000" price-max="1100000"
- Luxury focus: price-min="900000" (no max)

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Use functional components with hooks, NO class components
- Use 'use client' directive only when necessary (prefer Server Components)
- Keep components under 150 lines; split if larger
- Use semantic HTML elements (main, section, article, nav, header, footer)
- All images must have alt text with keyword optimization
- Implement lazy loading for images below the fold

